18 SECTION 17. IC 36-7-2.3 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
19 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
20 JULY 1, 2026]:
21 Chapter 2.3. Limits on Building and Construction Related Fees
22 Sec. 1. This chapter applies to a fee imposed by a unit for
23 approval of an application related to:
24 (1) construction or reconstruction of:
25 (A) residential buildings;
26 (B) commercial buildings;
27 (C) industrial buildings;
28 (D) any other building or building space; or
29 (E) an appurtenance to a building described in clauses (A)
30 through (D); or
31 (2) zoning, development, subdivision, classification, or
32 reclassification of land;
33 including a fee designated as a permit fee (including a fee for a
34 permit under IC 36-7-4-1109(f)), application fee, inspection fee,
35 processing fee, or by another name.
36 Sec. 2. As used in this chapter, "applicant" means a person who
37 submits an application that requires a fee described in section 1 of
38 this chapter.
39 Sec. 3. After December 31, 2026:
40 (1) Unless otherwise provided by law and subject to
41 subdivisions (2) and (3), a unit may not assess a fee in an
42 amount that is more than is reasonably necessary to cover the
EH 1001—LS 7120/DI 87

12
1 applicable cost to the unit to:
2 (A) process an application;
3 (B) inspect and review an applicant's plans; or
4 (C) prepare detailed statements for an applicant.
5 (2) Except as otherwise provided in this subdivision, any fee,
6 including a fee adopted before January 1, 2027, may be
7 increased:
8 (A) once every five (5) years; and
9 (B) by an amount not to exceed the combined annual
10 percentage change in the Consumer Price Index for all
11 Urban Consumers, as published by the United States
12 Bureau of Labor Statistics, for the preceding five (5) years.
13 However, if the cost to the unit substantially changes from the
14 amount described in subdivision (1), the legislative body of the
15 unit may adjust the fee to accurately reflect the cost to the
16 unit after conducting a public hearing.
17 (3) The total combined applicable fees for a particular Class
18 1 or Class 2 structure may not exceed two percent (2%) of the
19 construction costs of the applicable Class 1 or Class 2
20 structure. However, a unit may adopt an ordinance to opt out
21 of this subdivision.
22 (4) Any fee assessed and collected by a unit must be
23 maintained in a special fund dedicated solely to reimbursing
24 the costs actually incurred by the unit relating to the
25 imposition and amount of the fee. Each fund shall be
26 maintained as a separate line item in the unit's budget. Money
27 in the fund may not at any time revert to the general fund or
28 any other fund of the unit.
