22 SECTION 29. IC 36-7-4.3 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
23 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
24 1, 2026]:
25 Chapter 4.3. Increasing Housing Development
26 Sec. 1. This chapter does not apply to a unit that does not opt
27 out of the provisions that are applicable to the unit under
28 IC 36-7-4-201.3, IC 36-7-4.1, or IC 36-7-4.2.
29 Sec. 2. As used in this chapter, "unit" means a county, city, or
30 town.
31 Sec. 3. As used in this chapter, "UDO" means a unified
32 development ordinance.
33 Sec. 4. Not later than January 1, 2027, a unit conduct a public
34 hearing to review the UDO and any zoning regulations and land
35 development rules, with the goal of increasing housing
36 development by using the following factors:
37 (1) Providing for higher density development of duplexes,
38 triplexes, and fourplexes in areas designated for single family
39 homes.
40 (2) Constructing other housing types including accessory
41 dwelling units and manufactured and modular housing.
42 (3) Adaptive reuse of commercial buildings for residential use
EH 1001—LS 7120/DI 87

35
1 such as allowing multifamily development in retail, office, and
2 light manufacturing zones.
3 (4) Increasing the allowable floor area ratio in multifamily
4 housing areas.
5 (5) Waiving or eliminating regulations such as requirements
6 for:
7 (A) garage size and placement;
8 (B) steeper roof pitch;
9 (C) minimum lot size and square footage;
10 (D) greater setbacks;
11 (E) off-street parking;
12 (F) design standards that restrict or prohibit the use of
13 code compliant products; or
14 (G) property height limitations.
15 (6) Reviewing impact fee zones with zone advisory committee
16 for improvements.
17 (7) Streamlining or shortening the permitting processes and
18 timelines, including through one stop and parallel process
19 permitting by fifteen (15) days or more.
20 (8) Using property tax abatements to enable higher density
21 and mixed income communities.
22 (9) Donating vacant land for affordable housing development.
23 Sec. 5. Not later than January 1, 2027, the unit shall submit a
24 report to the executive director of legislative services agency by
25 electronic means under IC 5-14-6 that contains the following:
26 (1) If the unit:
27 (A) invested in a housing study in 2021, 2022, 2023, 2024,
28 or 2025; or
29 (B) had a housing study performed by a region's local
30 economic development organization;
31 a copy of the housing study.
32 (2) The minutes from the public hearing conducted under
33 section 4 of this chapter.
34 (3) Any newly developed or amended UDO as a result of the
35 review under section 4 of this chapter. The unit must provide
36 a written description of the ways in which the UDO was
37 changed to support increased housing development by using
38 some or all of the factors set forth in section 4 of this chapter.
